Will,
I had the same setup. I ground down the rotors on a bench grinder for the
five years I owned my '72, and never had a single problem. It was really
easy to do. I never used a rev limiting rotor, but I did miss a shift and
over reved the engine one time and one of the valve keepers came off.

Andy

